population.name: Study Population
population.description: Target population defined by eligibility criteria

objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective - Induction
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of intravenous (IV) ustekinumab in inducing clinical remission in subjects with moderately to severely active UC.

objectives.name: Primary Safety Objective - Induction
objectives.text: To evaluate the safety of IV ustekinumab in subjects with moderately to severely active UC.

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective - Endoscopic Healing (Induction)
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of IV ustekinumab in inducing endoscopic healing (ie, improvement in the endoscopic appearance of the mucosa) in subjects with moderately to severely active UC.

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective - Clinical Response (Induction)
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of IV ustekinumab in inducing clinical response in subjects with moderately to severely active UC.

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective - Quality of Life (Induction)
objectives.text: To evaluate the impact of IV ustekinumab on disease-specific health-related quality of life.

objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective - Maintenance
objectives.text: To evaluate clinical remission for SC maintenance regimens of ustekinumab in subjects with moderately to severely active UC induced into clinical response with ustekinumab.

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective - Maintenance of Clinical Response
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of ustekinumab in maintaining clinical response in subjects induced into clinical response with ustekinumab.

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective - Endoscopic Healing (Maintenance)
objectives.text: To evaluate endoscopic healing (ie, improvement in the endoscopic appearance of the mucosa) in subjects induced into clinical response with ustekinumab.

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective - Corticosteroid-free Remission
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of ustekinumab in achieving corticosteroid-free clinical remission in subjects induced into clinical response with ustekinumab.

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective - Maintenance of Clinical Remission
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of ustekinumab in maintaining clinical remission in subjects induced into clinical remission with ustekinumab.

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective - Bristol Stool Form Scale
objectives.text: To evaluate the performance of the Bristol Stool Form Scale score in the induction study.

endpoints.name: Major Secondary Induction Endpoint 3
endpoints.text: Change from induction baseline in the total score of the IBDQ at Week 8

endpoints.name: Major Secondary Maintenance Endpoint 1
endpoints.text: Maintenance of clinical response through Week 44

endpoints.name: Major Secondary Maintenance Endpoint 3
endpoints.text: Clinical remission and not receiving concomitant corticosteroids at Week 44

endpoints.name: Major Secondary Maintenance Endpoint 4
endpoints.text: Maintenance of clinical remission through Week 44 among the subjects who had achieved clinical remission at maintenance baseline

endpoints.name: Safety Endpoints
endpoints.text: Adverse events; clinical laboratory tests (chemistry and hematology); vital signs and physical examinations; a screening electrocardiogram; allergic reactions, infusion reactions and injection site reactions; and early detection of active tuberculosis.

endpoints.name: Exploratory Endpoint - Bristol Stool
endpoints.text: Average Bristol Stool Form Scale score over time in induction.

analysisPopulations.name: Primary Population
analysisPopulations.text: Subjects who are in clinical response to IV ustekinumab during induction will comprise the primary population in the maintenance study; this population will include the following: Subjects who are randomized to receive ustekinumab at Week 0 of the induction study and are in clinical response at I-8; Subjects who are randomized to receive placebo at Week 0 of the induction study and are not in clinical response at I-8, but are in clinical response at I-16 after receiving an induction dose of IV ustekinumab (~6 mg/kg) at I-8. Note that subjects who are delayed clinical responders to ustekinumab induction (i.e., the subjects who are randomized to ustekinumab at Week 0 of the induction study, not in clinical response at I-8 but are in clinical response at I-16 after receiving 1 dose of ustekinumab 90 mg SC at I-8) will not be included in the primary population.
analysisPopulations.label: Primary Population
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Subjects who are in clinical response to IV ustekinumab during induction will comprise the primary population in the maintenance study; this population will include the following: Subjects who are randomized to receive ustekinumab at Week 0 of the induction study and are in clinical response at I-8; Subjects who are randomized to receive placebo at Week 0 of the induction study and are not in clinical response at I-8, but are in clinical response at I-16 after receiving an induction dose of IV ustekinumab (~6 mg/kg) at I-8. Note that subjects who are delayed clinical responders to ustekinumab induction (i.e., the subjects who are randomized to ustekinumab at Week 0 of the induction study, not in clinical response at I-8 but are in clinical response at I-16 after receiving 1 dose of ustekinumab 90 mg SC at I-8) will not be included in the primary population.
analysisPopulations.criteria: In clinical response to IV ustekinumab induction (either at I-8 following IV induction or at I-16 following I-8 IV rescue) AND not a delayed responder receiving SC at I-8

analysisPopulations.name: Non-randomized Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: Includes subjects entering the maintenance study who will not be part of the primary population: Subjects who are in clinical response to placebo IV induction will receive placebo SC; Subjects who are delayed responders to ustekinumab induction will receive ustekinumab 90 mg SC q8w.
analysisPopulations.label: Non-randomized Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Includes subjects entering the maintenance study who will not be part of the primary population: Subjects who are in clinical response to placebo IV induction will receive placebo SC; Subjects who are delayed responders to ustekinumab induction will receive ustekinumab 90 mg SC q8w.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Clinical responders to placebo IV induction OR delayed responders to ustekinumab induction (responders at I-16 after SC dose at I-8)

titles.text: A Phase 3, Randomized, Double-blind, Placebo-controlled, Parallel-group, Multicenter Protocol to Evaluate the Safety and Efficacy of Ustekinumab Induction and Maintenance Therapy in Subjects with Moderately to Severely Active Ulcerative Colitis

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Corticosteroid stability
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: If receiving budesonide or beclomethasone dipropionate, the dose must have been stable for at least 2 weeks.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Corticosteroid/5-ASA discontinuation
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: If oral 5-ASA compounds or oral corticosteroids have been recently discontinued, they must have been stopped for at least 2 weeks.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Rectal corticosteroid discontinuation
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Rectal corticosteroids (ie, corticosteroids administered to the rectum or sigmoid colon via foam or enema or suppository) for at least 2 weeks.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: TNF-antagonist discontinuation
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: TNF-antagonist therapy (eg, infliximab, etanercept, certolizumab, adalimumab, golimumab [or approved biosimilars for these therapies]) for at least 8 weeks.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Adenomatous polyps screening
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: A subject 45 years of age must either have had a full colonoscopy to assess for the presence of adenomatous polyps within 5 years before the first administration of study agent or a full colonoscopy to assess for the presence of adenomatous polyps at the screening visit. The adenomatous polyps must be removed before the first administration of study agent.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Dysplasia/Malignancy screening
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: A subject who has had extensive colitis for 8 years, or disease limited to the left side of the colon for 10 years, must either have had a full colonoscopy to assess for the presence of dysplasia within 1 year before the first administration of study agent or a full colonoscopy to assess for the presence of malignancy at the screening visit.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Tuberculosis screening
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: All subjects will undergo QuantiFERON-TB Gold testing. In countries where the QuantiFERON-TB Gold test is not registered/approved, TB skin testing will also be required. A tuberculin skin test is recommended but not required for study centers in Ukraine if tuberculin is not available.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Laboratory parameters
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Has screening laboratory test results within the following parameters: a. Hemoglobin 8.0 g/dL (SI: 80.0 g/L); b. White blood cell count (WBC) 3  103 cells/L (SI: 3.0  109 cells/L); c. Neutrophils 1.5  103 cells /L (SI: 1.5  109 cells/L); d. Platelets 100  103 cells /L (SI: 100  109 cells/L); e. Serum creatinine 1.5 mg/dL (SI: 133 mol/L); f. Alanine aminotransferase (ALT) and aspartate aminotransferase (AST) concentrations must be within 2 times the upper limit of the normal range (ULN).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Apheresis exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Apheresis (eg, Adacolumn or Cellsorba apheresis) within 2 weeks before the first administration of study agent.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Hepatitis C exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Are seropositive for antibodies to hepatitis C virus (HCV) without a history of successful treatment, defined as being negative for HCV RNA at least 24 weeks after completing antiviral treatment.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Drug/Alcohol abuse exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Has a history of drug or alcohol abuse according to the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders, 5th edition (DSM-V), within 1 year before screening.

studyInterventions.name: Ustekinumab (CNTO1275)
studyInterventions.description: Fully human IgG1k monoclonal antibody to human IL-12/23p40.

studyInterventions.name: Placebo
studyInterventions.description: Matching IV and SC placebo for blinding.

studyInterventions.name: Oral 5-aminosalicylate (5-ASA)
studyInterventions.description: Must be maintained at a stable dose through induction.

studyInterventions.name: Oral corticosteroids
studyInterventions.description: Includes prednisone, budesonide, and beclomethasone dipropionate; stable dose required for induction.

studyInterventions.name: TNF-antagonist therapy
studyInterventions.description: Infliximab, adalimumab, golimumab, or approved biosimilars; must be discontinued 8 weeks prior.

studyInterventions.name: Vedolizumab
studyInterventions.description: Anti-alpha4beta7 integrin antagonist; must be discontinued prior to study.

commentAnnotations.text: Janssen Research & Development is a global organization that operates through different legal entities in various countries. The term 'sponsor' is used throughout the protocol to represent these various legal entities.

All subjects will undergo QuantiFERON-TB Gold testing. In countries where the QuantiFERON-TB Gold test is not registered/approved, TB skin testing will also be required (recommended but not required for study centers in Ukraine if tuberculin is not available).

studyDefinitionDocumentVersions.description: Substantial amendment to address health authority feedback and clarify LTE dosing.
Substantial amendment to address health authority requests for additional data collection (Bristol Stool Form Scale) and US-specific definitions.

studyAmendmentImpacts.description: Clarified and separated US-specific and global definitions of clinical remission for analysis populations.
Added Bristol Stool Form Scale as an exploratory objective and efficacy assessment in the induction study.
Modified TB skin testing requirements specifically for study centers in Ukraine.
Reordered secondary objectives and updated the analysis population for corticosteroid-free remission.
Clarified unblinding procedures for futility analysis and database locks.

studyAmendmentReasons.reasonText: To address health authority requests for additional data collection and provide further clarifications.
Address investigator feedback regarding protocol implementation.
Health authority requested collection of stool consistency data using the Bristol Stool Form Scale.
Tuberculin unavailability in Ukraine necessitated alternative testing guidance.

studyChanges.beforeText: Not explicitly separated by region in previous version.
studyChanges.afterText: The following US-specific definition of clinical remission will be used in the United States: an absolute stool number 3, a rectal bleeding subscore of 0, and a Mayo endoscopy subscore of 0 or 1.
To evaluate the data based on the Bristol Stool Form Scale score in the induction study.
studyChanges.summary: Added Bristol Stool Form Scale as an exploratory objective.

studyChanges.afterText: Inclusion Criterion 6e: If receiving budesonide or beclomethasone dipropionate, the dose must have been stable for at least 2 weeks.
studyChanges.summary: Added beclomethasone dipropionate to inclusion criteria for stable dosing.
Added International System of Units (SI) equivalents to laboratory parameters.
Clarified that a 'full' colonoscopy is required for subjects requiring screening for polyps or dysplasia.

studyChanges.beforeText: Exclusion 17: Seropositive for antibodies to HCV.
studyChanges.afterText: Exclusion 17: Are seropositive for antibodies to HCV without a history of successful treatment, defined as being negative for HCV RNA at least 24 weeks after completing antiviral treatment.
studyChanges.summary: Updated HCV exclusion to allow clinically cured subjects.
